{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'cat /task/task.md'","aggregated_output":"# SWE-bench Lite task: pallets__flask-5063\n\n**Repo:** pallets/flask  \n**Base commit (already checked out at /workspace):** `182ce3dd15dfa3537391c3efaf9c3ff407d134d4`\n\n## Problem statement\n\nFlask routes to return domain/sub-domains information\nCurrently when checking **flask routes** it provides all routes but **it is no way to see which routes are assigned to which subdomain**.\r\n\r\n**Default server name:**\r\nSERVER_NAME: 'test.local'\r\n\r\n**Domains (sub-domains):**\r\ntest.test.local\r\nadmin.test.local\r\ntest.local\r\n\r\n**Adding blueprints:**\r\napp.register_blueprint(admin_blueprint,url_prefix='',subdomain='admin')\r\napp.register_blueprint(test_subdomain_blueprint,url_prefix='',subdomain='test')\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ flask routes\r\n * Tip: There are .env or .flaskenv files present. Do \"pip install python-dotenv\" to use them.\r\nEndpoint                                                 Methods    Rule\r\n-------------------------------------------------------  ---------  ------------------------------------------------\r\nadmin_blueprint.home                                      GET        /home\r\ntest_subdomain_blueprint.home                             GET        /home\r\nstatic                                                    GET        /static/<path:filename>\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n**Feature request**\r\nIt will be good to see something like below (that will make more clear which route for which subdomain, because now need to go and check configuration).\r\n**If it is not possible to fix routes**, can you add or tell which method(s) should be used to get below information from flask? \r\n\r\n```\r\n$ flask routes\r\n * Tip: There are .env or .flaskenv files present. Do \"pip install python-dotenv\" to use them.\r\nDomain                Endpoint                                             Methods    Rule\r\n-----------------   ----------------------------------------------------  ----------  ------------------------------------------------\r\nadmin.test.local     admin_blueprint.home                                  GET        /home\r\ntest.test.local      test_subdomain_blueprint.home                         GET        /home\r\ntest.local           static                                                GET        /static/<path:filename>\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\n\n\n## Acceptance tests (must pass after your fix)\n\n- `tests/test_cli.py::TestRoutes::test_subdomain`\n- `tests/test_cli.py::TestRoutes::test_host`\n\n## Existing-test regressions to avoid\n\nMake sure these still pass: `tests/test_cli.py::TestRoutes` (all sibling tests).\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
